<F P=100> EAST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Progress in Scrapping Excess Weaponry Under CFE </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Progress in Scrapping Excess Weaponry Under CFE </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0104134594 Prague CESKY DENIK in Czech 30 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU0104134594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CESKY DENIK </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [CTK report: "Army Under Surveillance"] </F>
  [Text] Prague -- Representatives of countries that are 
signatories to the Treaty on Reducing Conventional Ground and 
Air Forces in Europe carried out 92 inspections in the Czech 
Army from 1 January 1993 to 1 March 1994. The inspections 
confirmed the Czech Republic's responsible approach to the 
implementation of the treaty. A total of 61 percent of the 
planned number of tanks, 57 percent of the armored combat 
vehicles, 48 percent of the artillery systems, and 62 percent of 
the combat aircraft had been destroyed by 1 March. Another 417 
tanks, 43 armored vehicles, 52 artillery systems, and 38 combat 
aircraft remain to be destroyed by 15 November 1995. 

</TEXT>

