<F P=100> EAST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Inspection Confirms Dismantling of 44 Tanks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Inspection Confirms Dismantling of 44 Tanks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0704080394 Prague CTK in English 1940 GMT 6 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0704080394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, April 6 (CTK) -- A NATO inspection team 
confirmed today that Slovakia has dismantled 44 tanks in 
accordance with an international treaty on reducing the number 
of conventional weapons in Europe. 
  According to a Vienna Convention on Reducing Conventional 
Arms in Europe, Slovakia must dismantle 423 tanks by November 
1995. 
  One of the 44 tanks was not dismantled or disarmed, but is 
destined for display in a museum. 
  According to the agreement, next year the Slovak Army should 
have 46,667 soldiers, 478 combat tanks, 683 armored vehicles, 
383 artillery pieces, 115 combat aircraft, and 25 combat 
helicopters. 

</TEXT>

