<F P=100> CENTRAL EURASIA </F>
<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Still Adamantly Refuting BW Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Still Adamantly Refuting BW Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Official Denies Charges </H4>

<F P=102> LD1404175394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1610 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1404175394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Grigoriy Karasin, an official representative of the 
Russian Foreign Ministry, dismissed on Thursday allegations by 
foreign media that Russia continues to work on the creation of 
biological weapons. 
  Such publications "are clearly aimed at destroying mutual 
trust, and at aggravating relations between the signatories of 
the Convention banning biological weapons," he said at a 
briefing in Moscow. 
  Karasin noted that Russia as legal successor of the USSR 
took 
all responsibility for the implementation of the 1972 
Convention, including the functions of a guarantor of this 
document. Under the trilateral agreements between Russia, USA 
and Great Britain, mutual visits to biological facilities and 
exchange of information continue between the sides. 
  Karasin also said that Russia is in favor of the creation of 
a control mechanism for the implementation of the Convention. A 
special conference on this issue will be convened in Geneva in 
September. 

</TEXT>

