<H3> <TI>   Prosecutor General Meets With Medellin Cartel Member `Popeye' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prosecutor General Meets With Medellin Cartel Member `Popeye' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2803034094 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2803034094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Prosecutor General Gustavo de Greiff today met with 
Medellin Cartel member John Jairo Velasquez, alias Popeye, in 
his office. The meeting was part of a process that includes 
negotiations on Popeye's sentence. Velasquez Vasquez was taken 
to the Prosecutor General's Office to enable him to take 
advantage of the surrender to justice program. 
  Popeye, Ottoniel de Jesus Gonzalez, alias Otto, and Roberto 
Escobar, alias El Osito, surrendered to authorities 18 months 
ago. Velasquez Vasquez met today with Prosecutor General Gustavo 
de Greiff, Deputy Prosecutor Francisco Sintura, and Ana Montes, 
the director of the Prosecutor's Office. This is the first time 
since his surrender that Popeye has agreed to negotiate with 
authorities. 
  The meeting lasted 90 minutes. The charges against him 
include drug trafficking, conspiracy, illegal enrichment, 
escaping from prison, and illegally possessing weapons. Amid 
tight security, Popeye was returned to Modelo Prison at around 
noon today. At the Prosecutor General's Office, Velasquez 
Vasquez expressed his wish to cooperate with justice and to 
confess to the crimes in which he has participated. 
  [Begin recording] [Sintura] He surrendered to justice and is 
working through the process. 
  [Reporter] Has he already confessed to some crimes? 
  [Sintura] We are working on this. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

