  [Text] Alberto Urdinola Grajales, older brother of 
confessed drug traffickers Ivan and Julio Fabio Urdinola, was 
killed by gunshot early this morning in a Cali discotheque. No 
one has been arrested yet. 
  Early this morning at the Chaparrito Disco, located in 
southern Cali, Alberto Urdinola Grajales was killed. He was the 
older brother of Ivan and Julio, who have surrendered to justice 
based on Article 37 of the new Criminal Code. 
  Official sources reported a brawl had occurred at the crime 
site. Four young men made a flirtatious remark to a woman who 
was sitting with Urdinola. Urdinola bit the ear of one of the 
young men who in turn shot him. 
  [Begin unidentified speaker recording] The body was taken to 
Remedios Clinic after we went to the site and followed normal 
procedures. [end recording] 
  Meanwhile, the Prosecutor's Office has said Urdinola did not 
have a criminal record. The authorities said no one had been 
arrested for the crime. 

