<F P=106> [Report by Armando Solis M.] </F>
  [Text] Torreon, Coahuila, 28 March -- Federal Judicial 
Police [PJF] personnel today seized more than four tons of 
cocaine and arrested two alleged drug traffickers who were 
transporting the drug in a tanker truck on the road from this 
city to Concepcion del Oro, Zacatecas. 
  PJF Commander Juan Carlos Alvarado reported Raul Juarez de 
la 
Paz and Miguel Angel Salazar Ramirez, both from Uruapan, 
Michoacan, had been arrested during the police action. Both men 
testified that they received the merchandise in Guadalajara, 
Jalisco and were taking it to Cadereyta, Nuevo Leon. 
  The policemen initially stopped the truck for speeding on 
the 
road to Concepcion del Oro in Zacatecas and discovered the large 
cocaine shipment while checking the vehicle. The 4,187 kg of 
cocaine had been placed in 2,162 packages in the vehicle's tank. 
  The PJF commander said the drug shipment and the two men 
were 
placed in the custody of the Federal Attorney General's Office 
in Saltillo, Coahuila. 

