BFN 

  [Text] The Yen Bai provincial people's committee recently 
burned 38 kg of confiscated opium at the 19 May Square in Yen 
Bai City. This is the fourth time the province has destroyed a 
large volume of opium since its implementation of the 
government's program on preventing and opposing drug addiction. 
  While striving to destroy opium, the province has actively 
detected and arrested those who engage in drug trafficking. 
Recently, the province monitored and arrested the driver of a 
car with 43.7 kg of opium. 

