<F P=103> NC2703202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by News Research and Commentary Group] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] In the campaign against 
narcotics, law enforcement forces discovered and seized a total 
of 90 tons of various drugs and arrested 459 ringleaders of 
smuggling bands. In intelligence operations, two tons of 
narcotics bound for Europe were discovered. In the 11 months of 
1372, 65 cases of clashes with insurgents and smugglers 
occurred, mostly in Sistan va Baluchestan, Kerman, and southern 
Khorasan. During this period, 14,600 smugglers were arrested 
and 43,000 addicts were sent to prison. The discoveries in the 
year 1372 register an increase compared to the corresponding 
period of the preceding year. The deputy secretary general of 
the United Nations and the director of narcotics control 
commended the activities of the Islamic Republic of Iran during 
the past year in its campaign against the transit of drugs. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

