<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Drug Arrests, Seizures for 13-24 March </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Roundup of Drug Arrests, Seizures for 13-24 March </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2603153694 </F>
<F P=103> TA2603153694 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 
1200 GMT on 13 March reports that "29-year-old Tzvi Oren from 
Tel Aviv was apprehended five days ago at Ben-Gurion Airport in 
possession of over 1.5 kg of cocaine and thousands of Ecstasy 
pills. The Tel Aviv Magistrate's Court today remanded him into 
custody for two weeks and canceled a decree banning the 
publication of details about the affair." 
  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1300 GMT on 15 March 
reports that "the Police Central District's drug squad yesterday 
captured five members of a gang which smuggled 8 kg of heroin 
into Israel from Turkey. Central District Command Asaf Hefetz 
said that the five are the chief smugglers of the drug into 
Israel. The drugs were found in a hiding place near Ben-Gurion 
Airport." 
  An ITIM report on page 3 of Jerusalem THE JERUSALEM POST in 
English on 23 March notes that "two long time drug dealers who 
conspired to smuggle a ton of cocaine into the country from 
Colombia, were sentenced yesterday in Tel Aviv District Court. 
In a plea bargain arrangement, 'Amos Solmi, 42, of Giv'atayim, 
also convicted of smuggling heroin from Turkey, was sentenced to 
18 years in prison. Yuval Shemesh, 31, who generally lives in 
Colombia, was sentenced to 7 and 1/2 years after agreeing to 
testify against other drug dealers." 
  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1000 GMT on 24 March 
reports that "customs inspectors at Ben-Gurion Airport last 
night captured 2 kg of cocaine in the belongings of a U.S. 
citizen. The worth of the cocaine is estimated at $2 million." 

</TEXT>

