<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> NIGERIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Task Force Outlines `New' Strategies To Curb Drug Trafficking </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Task Force Outlines `New' Strategies To Curb Drug Trafficking </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2903223594 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1500 GMT 
29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2903223594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The task force on hard drugs has mapped out new 
strategies to eradicate drug trafficking. They include the use 
of lectures, conferences, seminars, as well as symposia and a 
massive public enlightenment campaign to educate the public on 
the consequences of drug abuse. In addition, more tribunals 
have to be set up throughout the country to try drug offenders. 
The chairman of the task force, Brigadier General (Ishaya 
Bamaiyi), gave the information yesterday in Lagos when members 
of the task force visited some foreign embassies and high 
commissions in the country. He advised the international 
community to assist the federal government in its efforts to 
eradicate drug abuse. 

</TEXT>

