<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Largest Haul Ever' of LSD in Southern Cape Area Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Largest Haul Ever' of LSD in Southern Cape Area Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB0304113494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0841 GMT 3 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB0304113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cape Town April 3 SAPA -- Detectives of the 
Narcotics Branch in the Southern Cape have confiscated the 
largest haul of LSD ever recovered in the area, SABC [South 
African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reports. Acting on 
information received, the team, led by Capt Gordon Lamstra, 
raided a house in Long Ships Road, Plettenberg Bay, where the 
LSD and dagga [marijuana] valued at more than R[Rand]3,000 was 
found. A Johannesburg man, Mr Derek John Nel, was arrested and 
charged with dealing in drugs. He was released on R1,000 bail. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

