<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Police Seize 315 Kg of Hashish, Uncover Smuggling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Narcotics Police Seize 315 Kg of Hashish, Uncover Smuggling </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Ring 

<F P=102>   AU3003172894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1347 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU3003172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 30/3/1994 -- The narcotics 
police uncovered about 315 kilograms of hashish hidden at the 
residence of a Romanian citizen in the Maramures County, 
north-western Romania. The drug was found packed in several 
hundred parcels tin-veiled [as received], inscripted in Italian 
language, and buried in the garden. 
  The police discovered also under the kitchen floor of a home 
in another village in the Maramures County a Dutch made vacuum 
packing machine suspected to be employed in drugs packing. 
  While continuing investigations in this area at the 
north-western border of Romania, the police uncovered an entire 
ring of drugs smugglers. Some other inhabitants of the same 
county are suspected to be involved in trafficking a great deal 
of hashish coming from Lebanon to Constanta, Romanian port at 
the Black Sea. After a short leg to the packing machine, the 
hashish was being sent to the Netherlands, crossing the Romanian 
border in trucks loaded with apples and wine. Over 5 tonnes of 
hashish are believed to have been conveyed to the Netherlands in 
three trucks. The investigation continues with some of the 
suspects placed under arrest. 

</TEXT>

