  [Text] The Dutch, Belgian, and French police forces carried 
out a joint anti-drug operation on Friday night [25 March]. 
  Over 1,000 vehicles were stopped for controls on Dutch, 
Belgian, and French highways in an operation involving 700 
police and customs officers. 
  Seventy dealers and nine drug users were arrested in the 
course of the operation. 
  The Dutch police described the joint operation as a success 
and said they did not rule out similar cooperation in the future. 

