<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Signs Protocol With Turkish Counterpart </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister Signs Protocol With Turkish Counterpart </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0104171794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0905 
GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0104171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Feoktistov] </F>
  [Text] Ankara, 1 April -- The talks between Russian and 
Turkish Interior Ministers Viktor Yerin and Nahit Mentese 
yesterday ended in Ankara by signing a joint protocol. 
  The sides confirmed their agreement and resoluteness to 
develop cooperation between the two countries in the fight 
against international terrorism and drug smuggling. During the 
talks the decision was taken to hold a meeting of the joint 
commission in the very near future with the aim of stepping up 
mutual actions in the security field. 
  Speaking at the protocol signing ceremony, Mentese said 
strengthening cooperation between Turkey and Russia on the basis 
of friendship and unity of interests would be for the benefit of 
both states. 
  The Russian and Turkish Interior Ministries, Yerin said in 
his turn, agreed to coordinate actions in the fight against 
organized crime. According to the Russian minister, special 
attention was given to drugs and arms smuggling. 
  It is expected that the Russian delegation will leave Turkey 
today. 

</TEXT>

