<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Consultation"] </F>
  [Text] A regional conference of leaders of Volga Region 
organs of prosecutor's offices, internal affairs, and 
counterintelligence has been held in Kazan. 
  Representatives of Bashkiria, the Mari Republic, Mordovia, 
Tatarstan, Udmurtia, Chuvashia, and Nizhniy Novgorod, Orenburg, 
Samara, and Ulyanovsk Oblasts participated in it. The topic of 
the conference was the struggle against organized crime, drugs 
trafficking, and the illegal circulation of weapons. 
  Measures were devised which envisage cooperation between the 
ministries and departments in neighboring regions. An appeal 
has been adopted to the Federal Assembly and the Russian 
Federation president to immediately produce and adopt a package 
of legislative acts designed to combat organized crime, 
corruption, drugs trafficking, and the illegal circulation of 
weapons. 

