<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Roundup for 29 March-7 April </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Narcotics Roundup for 29 March-7 April </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804032394 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804032394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
fileworthy reports on counternarcotics operations in countries 
monitored by FBIS London Bureau from 31 March-7 April. Sources 
are given in parentheses at the end of each report. 
<H5>  Denmark </H5>
  What is described as "the largest drug haul so far" was 
carried out in Denmark. Police discovered 1.5 tonnes of hashish 
in a Danish vessel that was inspected off the island of Fyn. 
The police suspect that about 11 tonnes of hashish was removed 
from the boat before the raid. During the raid, 18 Danish 
citizens were arrested. The vessel with the cargo of hashish 
was apparently on its way from North Africa. (Helsinki Suomen 
Yleisradio Network in Finnish 1000 GMT 5 Apr 94) 
<H5>  Iran </H5>
  Brigadier General Seyfollahi, commander of the Law 
Enforcement Forces, reports that nearly 2,800 kg of a variety of 
narcotic substances had been seized from bandits and smugglers 
and the offenders arrested during the brief period since the 
start of the new year. (Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of 
Iran First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 3 Apr 94) 
  Law enforcement forces seized 144 kgs of different types of 
narcotics during the week beginning March 21. According to the 
deputy head of the ideological department of the forces, 49 
people were arrested in this connection. (Tehran IRNA in 
English 1121 GMT 31 Mar 94) 
<H5>  Russia </H5>
  Sixteen soldiers belonging to a Russian strategic missile 
unit in the city of Kopeysk were detained while buying hard 
drugs from a local dealer, the counterintelligence department 
for the Chelyabinsk region reported on 7 April. 
Counterintelligence officers searched the dealer's apartment 
and found eight kg of drugs. (Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1029 
GMT 7 Apr 94) 
<H5>  Spain </H5>
  The Civil Guard and the police seized 33 kilos of cocaine 
and 
arrested seven people in three different searches conducted at 
Madrid-Barajas airport between 1400 and 2000 on 3 April. 
(Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 2000 GMT 3 Apr 94) 
<H5>  Ukraine </H5>
  A 31 March news release by the presidential cabinet press 
service reports that Ukraine's Customs House seized 98 kilos of 
drug-containing raw materials from 23-29 March. (Kiev Radio 
Ukraine World Service in English 2100 GMT 31 Mar 94) 
<H5>  United Kingdom </H5>
  Customs and Excise officers raided a house in West 
Hampstead, 
north London, on 5 April and seized 30 kilos of heroin worth 3 
million pounds. Three men--two from Turkey and one from 
Mauritius--were arrested. (London PRESS ASSOCIATION English 
1300 GMT 6 Apr 94) 

</TEXT>

