  [Text] Three members of a syndicate recruiting youngsters 
to export hard drugs have been arrested in Lagos by the National 
Drug Law Enforcement Agency. The chairman of the task force on 
hard drugs, Brigadier General Musa Baaniyi, made this known in a 
statement. He said the syndicate had recruited a 17-year-old 
student, who was arrested at Murtala Mohamed Airport, to export 
hard drugs to the United States. Gen. Baaniyi appealed to 
parents, guardians, and school principals to monitor the 
activities of their students at all times. He advised those 
with children or wards possessing international passports to 
ensure the safekeeping of the document. 

