<H3> <TI>   Colombian Foreign Minister Visits, Discusses Antidrug </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Colombian Foreign Minister Visits, Discusses Antidrug </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Measures 

<F P=102>   LD0904165694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1554 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Gennadiy Kochuk] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 9 TASS -- Bogota is ready to share its 
experience in anti-drug trafficking measures with Moscow, 
Colombian Foreign Minister Nohemi Sanin Posada de Rubio told 
ITAR-TASS today. 
  The minister had a meeting with correspondents at the 
Russian 
Foreign Ministry's Diplomatic Academy. 
  Colombia understands Russian concern over the fact Russia 
has 
attracted drug dealers, said Nohemi Sanin. Colombia has been 
taking anti-drug trafficking measures for many years and has 
gained certain experience in this sphere it is ready to share 
with Russia. 
  Drug business can be counteracted with joint measures, which 
are envisaged by the treaty on fundamentals of bilateral 
relations signed by Nojemi Sanin and Andrey Kozyrev on results 
of their negotiations. 

</TEXT>

