<F P=101></F>
<H3> <TI>     Turkish, Ukrainian Interior Ministers Sign Agreement To </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish, Ukrainian Interior Ministers Sign Agreement To </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Fight   Drugs, Other Crimes 

<F P=102> TA1504192694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1504192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Official talks were held between Turkey and Ukraine 
in Ankara today to develop security cooperation. The two 
countries signed an agreement on cooperation against crime. The 
agreement was signed by Interior Minister Nahit Mentese and 
Ukrainian Internal Affairs Minister Andriy Vasylyshyn. 
  In a statement at the signing ceremony, Mentese said the 
agreement envisages effective and comprehensive cooperation 
between the two countries in fighting international narcotics 
smuggling, international terrorism, and other organized crimes. 
Mentese reported that it was decided to establish a joint 
committee with representatives from the two sides to supervise 
the cooperation and eliminate shortcomings. 
  In his statement, Vasylyshyn declared that the two countries 
will undertake broad cooperation in the security field, 
including the struggle against the terrorist PKK [Workers Party 
of Kurdistan] organization. 
  The Ukrainian minister concluded his contacts in Ankara and 
left for Istanbul. He was seen off at Ankara's Esenboga Airport 
by Mentese. Vasylyshyn will leave Turkey on 17 April. 

</TEXT>

