BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on regional narcotics developments monitored through 15 
April. 
  Colombia 
  On 7 April, police seized 12 kg of coca paste near the 
border 
between Caldas and Risaralda Departments. (Santa Fe de Bogota EL 
TIEMPO in Spanish 8 Apr 94 p 16A) 
  The Colombian Army captured 120 drug traffickers and 
confiscated more than 10 tons of cocaine from January to April, 
according to a Defense Ministry communique. The Army also 
seized 14,952 gallons of acetone, 11 tons of caustic soda, and 
three tons of cement found in clandestine laboratories. In 
addition, four tons of marijuana were seized and 15 hectares 
planted with it were razed. (Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 2141 
GMT 13 Apr 94) 
  Narcotics police have cratered three clandestine landing 
strips in Caqueta Department. The airstrips were being used by 
Colombian, Bolivian, and Peruvian drug traffickers. (Madrid EFE 
in Spanish 1928 GMT 13 Apr 94) 
  Costa Rica 
  Police have recently disabled three domestic cocaine 
distribution networks, captured 10 drug traffickers, and 
confiscated more than 2 kg of cocaine and crack. (Panama City 
ACAN in Spanish 2015 GMT 13 Apr 94) 
  Guatemala 
  Counternarcotics agents have confiscated 20 kg of high-grade 
cocaine, valued at 2 million quetzales, and have arrested two 
Guatemalans and one Colombian in Guatemala City. (Guatemala City 
LA REPUBLICA in Spanish 13 Apr 94 p 8) 
  Treasury Police have captured two people and located and 
destroyed a field planted with marijuana in Olopa, Chiquimula 
Department. (Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 11 Apr 94 p 
24) 
  Panama 
  The Technical Judicial Police's Drug Secretariat has burned 
795 kg of confiscated cocaine. (Panama City Circuito RPC 
Television in Spanish 2300 GMT 15 Apr 94) 
  The Customs Directorate has arrested U.S. citizen Norma 
Gibson and daughter Olivia Tarona Mahon after they were found to 
be in possession of 2 kg of cocaine worth $70,000. The 
directorate has seized more than 300 kg of cocaine so far this 
year. (Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2247 GMT 11 Apr 94) 
  Cristobal Fundora, director of the National Air Service, has 
reported that fields of marijuana have been spotted from the air 
in the areas of Bocas del Toro, Punta Burica, and the Perlas 
Archipelago. He added that all of these areas will be sprayed 
to wipe out the fields. (Panama City EL SIGLO in Spanish 14 Apr 
94 p 12) 
  Inspector Ramiro Jarvis, head of the Technical Judicial 
Police's Narcotics Division, has reported that 400 kg of cocaine 
have been seized so far this year. In 1993, the office seized 
approximately 5.45 metric tons. More than 14 metric tons of 
narcotics have been confiscated over the past two years. (Panama 
City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in Spanish 14 Apr 94 p C6) 
  Venezuela 
  Street sales of narcotics have earned drug traffickers $520 
million in the first quarter of this year. During the same 
period, police seized 2.5 metric tons of cocaine. Deputy Luis 
Emilio Rondon, head of the Counternarcotics Commission in the 
Chamber of Deputies, says this figure is alarming because in the 
same period in 1993, drug mafias only netted $140 million. 
(Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0008 GMT 14 Apr 94) 
  Deputy Rondon has reported that more than 2.5 metric tons of 
cocaine and 765 kg of marijuana were confiscated in the first 
quarter of 1994. Rondon opened a debate on drugs and drug 
trafficking in Venezuela by drawing attention to the threatening 
magnitude of drug trafficking in the country. (Caracas EL 
UNIVERSAL in Spanish 13 Apr 94 p 1-13) 
  Colombian citizen Mauricio Uribe has been arrested in 
Tachira 
department with 2 kg of cocaine found hidden in a suitcase. 
(Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in Spanish 1550 GMT 13 
Apr 94) 

</TEXT>

