<H3> <TI>   Cuban, Peruvian Foreign Ministers Sign Antidrug Agreement, </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuban, Peruvian Foreign Ministers Sign Antidrug Agreement, </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Customs   Accord 

<F P=102> FL1204125494 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1204125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Roberto Cavada Barrera] </F>
  [Excerpt] On 11 April, Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto 
Robaina ratified in Peru an antidrug trafficking agreement and a 
customs accord between Cuban and Peruvian customs services. 
Robaina and Peruvian Foreign Minister Efrain Goldenberg signed 
the agreements at the closing of an official meeting at the 
Torre Tagle Palace. The meeting between Robaina and Goldenberg, 
who is also Peru's prime minister, lasted 45 minutes. Goldenberg 
granted us an exclusive interview for Radio Rebelde's 
``Exclusive'' program: 
  [Begin recording] Goldenberg: This is 
just one more step in the long friendship that unites Peru and 
Cuba. We are ready to engage in other issues and continue to 
make progress. 
  Cavada: Are you pleased with Foreign Minister 
Robaina's visit? 
  Goldenberg: Of course. [end recording] 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

