<H3> <TI>   Carles Alleges U.S. `Authorized' Drug Trafficking, Money </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Carles Alleges U.S. `Authorized' Drug Trafficking, Money </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Laundering   in Panama 

<F P=102> PA1404011394 Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in Spanish 13 
Apr 94 p 40 </F>

<F P=103> PA1404011394 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Esteban Huertas G.] </F>
  [Text] Ruben Dario Carles, Change '94 presidential 
candidate, said during an impromptu news conference in the lobby 
of the Europa Hotel yesterday that ``the U.S. Government has 
authorized drug trafficking and money laundering in Panama for 
some years now.'' He also said ``the charges against Panama are 
unfair.'' 
  Carles acknowledged ``money laundering is taking place in 
Panama more so now than during the past regime.'' 
  According to Carles ``this activity belittles the country's 
image throughout the world.'' According to Carles ``President 
Guillermo Endara's administration has ample means to defend 
itself from the attacks imposed by U.S. policies.'' 
  Carles said ``we Panamanians cannot accept the U.S. charges, 
but we must condemn the performance of certain court officials, 
judges, district attorneys, the Prosecutor's Office, and certain 
institutions responsible for curbing drug trafficking.'' 
  Regarding the discrediting of certain Panamanian 
organizations involved in the struggle against money laundering 
and drug trafficking, Carles said ``we must improve the 
tarnished image of official institutions by implementing 
measures aimed at ensuring officials' performance so as to 
prevent them from submitting to this illegal activity.'' 

</TEXT>

