<H3> <TI>   Nearly Five Tons of Opium Reportedly Seized in </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nearly Five Tons of Opium Reportedly Seized in </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Sistan-Baluchestan 

<F P=102>   LD1404174894 Tehran IRNA in English 1223 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1404174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Ahwaz, Khuzestan Prov. April, 14, IRNA -- The law 
enforcement personnel have seized nearly five tons of narcotic 
drugs after armed clashes with drug traffickers and bandits in 
the southeastern province of Sistan-Baluchestan over the past 
two days, it was announced here Thursday. 
  Commander of the law enforcement personnel, Brigadier 
General 
Reza Seyfollahi, said his forces also seized several firearms 
from the drug traffickers. He added that the haul included 
4,700 kgs of opium and some 20 kgs of morphine. 
  According to him, the amount of drugs seized from 
traffickers 
in 1992 and 1993 stood at 65 tons and 95 tons respectively. 
  Referring to the admission of the U.S. Administration to its 
inability to fight drug trafficking at home, Seyfollahi said the 
campaign against narcotics in Iran is so tough and so serious 
that even the UN, which is under Washington's influence, has had 
to admit that Iran's campaign against narcotics must be a model 
for other countries to follow. 

</TEXT>

