<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> NIGERIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Nongovernmental Organization To Combat Drug Trafficking, </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Nongovernmental Organization To Combat Drug Trafficking, </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Abuse   Established 

<F P=102> AB1704151394 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 0600 GMT 
17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1704151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lagos Radio Nigeria Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
BFN 

  [Text] A nongovernmental organization aimed at combatting 
drug abuse and trafficking in Africa has been set up in Lagos. 
It is known as the Society for the Eradication of Drug Abuse in 
Africa, SEDA. A statement by the organization says the 
continent is becoming a major drug consumption center with 
health and social consequences. As part of its plans to combat 
the problem, SEDA is organizing an international conference on 
drug abuse and trafficking. It will also embark on visits to 
prisons and hospitals in parts of the world to offer counseling 
to jailed drug couriers. 

</TEXT>

